WEBVTT

00:05.200 --> 00:06.200 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening.

00:06.200 --> 00:08.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:08.200 --> 00:11.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
On the "NewsHour" tonight:
Senate Republicans make public
a revised plan to take the place

00:11.733 --> 00:13.433 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of Obamacare.

00:13.433 --> 00:17.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
What's inside the bill,
and can it win enough
votes to become law?

00:17.300 --> 00:19.366 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Then:

00:19.366 --> 00:22.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP, President of the
United States: From a practical
standpoint, most people would

00:22.300 --> 00:24.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
have taken that meeting.

00:24.400 --> 00:28.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: President
Trump in France defends
his son's meeting with
a Russian government

00:30.166 --> 00:33.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
lawyer in the hopes of
getting opposition research
on Hillary Clinton.

00:35.800 --> 00:38.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And our series Inside Putin's
Russia continues with a look
at enemies of the state and how

00:40.100 --> 00:42.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Russia's leaders
responds to dissent.

00:42.133 --> 00:47.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
VLADIMIR KARA-MURZA, Open
Russia: I felt just life slowly
going out of the whole body.

00:48.600 --> 00:51.000 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I remember that distinct
feeling that, this is it.

00:51.000 --> 00:52.500 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
This is the end.

00:52.500 --> 00:57.466 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All that and more
on tonight's "PBS NewsHour."

00:59.033 --> 01:01.333 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

01:01.333 --> 01:06.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: It is the
Senate Republican health
care bill version 2.0.

01:12.666 --> 01:17.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Party leaders made it public
today, but the path to passage
remained anything but clear.

01:18.866 --> 01:20.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Our Lisa Desjardins
begins our coverage.

01:20.266 --> 01:22.233 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

01:22.233 --> 01:24.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MITCH MCCONNELL (R-KY),
Majority Leader: So, it's
time to rise to the occasion.

01:24.133 --> 01:26.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: A
critical moment for
health care and Congress.

01:26.800 --> 01:31.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Majority Leader Mitch McConnell
unveiled Senate Republicans'
second-draft bill, hoping it

01:32.966 --> 01:34.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
can win the minimum
50 votes he needs.

01:34.366 --> 01:36.433 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

01:36.433 --> 01:39.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MITCH MCCONNELL: The revised
draft improves on the previous
version in a number of ways,

01:39.133 --> 01:44.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
all while retaining the
fundamental goals of
providing stability and
improving affordability.

01:44.066 --> 01:46.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
LISA DESJARDINS:
What has changed?

01:46.733 --> 01:50.466 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
First, it keeps two Obamacare
taxes on the wealthy.

01:50.466 --> 01:55.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Second, it uses that money,
in part, to add more than over
$100 billion in new spending;

01:57.433 --> 02:01.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
$70 billion would go to insurers
to stabilize markets and bring
down out-of-pocket costs,

02:03.200 --> 02:05.733 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and $45 billion would
fight the opioid epidemic.

02:05.733 --> 02:10.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
On Medicaid, the bill still cuts
future spending significantly,
but does give states more leeway

02:12.133 --> 02:15.700 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to expand who is
eligible for the program.

02:15.700 --> 02:20.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But perhaps the biggest change
is the addition of a proposal
by Texas Senator Ted Cruz.

02:22.733 --> 02:26.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The so-called Cruz amendment
would let insurers mostly opt
out of all Affordable Care Act

02:26.966 --> 02:29.066 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
requirements.

02:29.066 --> 02:32.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
They could potentially
offer cheaper bare-bones
plans, as long as they
offer a few plans that

02:34.100 --> 02:36.800 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
do meet Obamacare standards.

02:36.800 --> 02:39.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
At the same time,
other Republicans are
crafting their own ideas.

02:39.866 --> 02:41.400 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

02:41.400 --> 02:43.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
LINDSEY GRAHAM (R), South
Carolina: Well, you know.

02:43.433 --> 02:45.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We're going to support Mitch's
effort with his new plan,
but we want an alternative,

02:45.500 --> 02:47.566 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and we're going to see
which one can get 50 votes.

02:47.566 --> 02:48.800 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We're not undercutting Mitch.

02:48.800 --> 02:50.833 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
He's not undercutting us.

02:50.833 --> 02:54.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Senators
Lindsey Graham of South Carolina
and Bill Cassidy of Louisiana

02:54.400 --> 02:58.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
say their amendment would send
more money directly to states.

02:58.300 --> 03:00.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
It's not clear how
much support that has.

03:00.900 --> 03:01.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
As for Democrats:

03:01.900 --> 03:03.933 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

03:03.933 --> 03:05.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHUCK SCHUMER (D-NY), Minority
Leader: It appears that
little has changed at the core

03:05.633 --> 03:07.633 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of the bill.

03:07.633 --> 03:10.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Minority Leader
Chuck Schumer says Republicans
will still have a problem

03:10.966 --> 03:13.700 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
getting some key members of
their own party on board.

03:13.700 --> 03:15.666 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

03:15.666 --> 03:18.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHUCK SCHUMER: Moderate
Republicans looking at this bill
should be able to see that the

03:18.633 --> 03:23.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
incredibly modest change to
the tax provisions, the small
pot of funding for opioid abuse

03:25.600 --> 03:30.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
treatment, these other tweaks
around the edges are like a
drop in the bucket, compared to

03:31.966 --> 03:36.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
what the bill does to Medicaid,
to seniors, to Americans
with preexisting conditions.

03:38.766 --> 03:42.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: All sides
are now waiting for a pivotal
report, the analysis of the

03:42.633 --> 03:45.600 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
bill by the nonpartisan
Congressional Budget Office.

03:45.600 --> 03:48.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Especially waiting is Wisconsin
Senator Ron Johnson, a key vote.

03:48.133 --> 03:49.500 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

03:49.500 --> 03:51.466 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
RON JOHNSON (R), Wisconsin:
Show me your math.

03:51.466 --> 03:53.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Show me what the
first baseline was.

03:53.400 --> 03:56.566 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Show me what the policy
results in terms of spending.

03:56.566 --> 04:00.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Republicans
have not yet announced
when they will hold a vote.

04:00.633 --> 04:03.133 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Leaders had hoped for next week.

04:03.133 --> 04:07.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And of the 52 Senate
Republicans, we already
know that two of them
are no-votes on this

04:07.666 --> 04:09.133 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
latest draft.

04:09.133 --> 04:11.733 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That's Susan Collins of Maine
and Rand Paul of Kentucky.

04:11.733 --> 04:15.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Judy, of course, that means
Mitch McConnell cannot lose
any more Republicans, and there

04:15.933 --> 04:17.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
are many on the fence.

04:17.166 --> 04:18.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Wow.

04:18.466 --> 04:19.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
So, Lisa, thank you.

04:19.466 --> 04:21.466 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And, of course, stay here.

04:21.466 --> 04:24.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We're going to bring in Julie
Rovner, who we know well,
chief correspondent, Washington

04:24.966 --> 04:28.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
correspondent, for Kaiser
Health News, joining us too.

04:28.533 --> 04:30.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I'm going to start
with you, Julie.

04:30.466 --> 04:34.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, there have been some
changes, as Lisa just reported,
to Medicaid, a few, but not

04:36.033 --> 04:37.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
enough to satisfy
these moderates.

04:37.933 --> 04:39.366 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
What exactly did they do?

04:39.366 --> 04:40.766 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JULIE ROVNER, Kaiser
Health News: That's right.

04:40.766 --> 04:42.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The moderates have been
unhappy with the Medicaid cuts.

04:42.833 --> 04:47.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Senator Susan Collins, who, as
we just heard, is already a no,
came out and said, the changes

04:47.500 --> 04:50.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that they would make to
Medicaid go beyond repealing
the Affordable Care Act.

04:50.933 --> 04:55.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Medicaid was expanded in the
Affordable Care Act, but these
changes would actually cap

04:55.033 --> 04:58.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the program, something
Republicans have been trying
to do since the 1980s.

04:58.400 --> 05:00.333 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It's for the conservatives.

05:00.333 --> 05:02.466 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Moderates are still unhappy.

05:02.466 --> 05:05.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
As Lisa pointed out, there
is a little bit more money
to deal with opioid abuse.

05:05.966 --> 05:08.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
They can get out of
the caps if there's a
public health emergency.

05:08.833 --> 05:11.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But those are pretty
much all the changes
that they have made here.

05:11.100 --> 05:12.900 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And how is
all this going over, Lisa?

05:12.900 --> 05:14.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
LISA DESJARDINS: Right.

05:14.266 --> 05:16.500 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
There are a lot of big
question marks on Capitol Hill.

05:16.500 --> 05:19.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think that you have got
the same question marks
on the right and the left.

05:19.566 --> 05:24.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
They tried to bring in
moderates, and including
giving them the ability
to increase -- the

05:25.966 --> 05:28.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
states could increase who
can be under Medicaid.

05:28.033 --> 05:30.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But there's not as much money
to do it, so you would have
to make a choice between the

05:30.800 --> 05:35.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
number of people you could cover
under Medicaid and how much you
would give them in benefits.

05:37.800 --> 05:40.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It doesn't really address
questions of the overall need
for health care some of these

05:40.066 --> 05:42.600 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
moderates have.

05:42.600 --> 05:45.866 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Now,
Julie, we heard in Lisa's
report the reference to
what Senator Ted Cruz

05:45.866 --> 05:49.900 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
has wanted, has to do with
giving states more options.

05:49.900 --> 05:52.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Describe exactly
what that involves.

05:52.366 --> 05:54.400 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JULIE ROVNER: Well,
Senator Cruz and a number
of the conservatives
in the House too have

05:54.400 --> 05:57.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
complained that one of
the biggest problems
with the Affordable
Care Act is that people

05:57.433 --> 06:02.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
who buy their own insurance are
finding themselves paying much
more, more both in premiums and

06:02.100 --> 06:03.233 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
in out-of-pocket spending.

06:03.233 --> 06:05.300 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And he wants to help people.

06:05.300 --> 06:07.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But basically the way he would
do it is, he would say, for
healthy people, if you want

06:07.700 --> 06:12.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
to buy fewer benefits,
you can do that, and you
would get less coverage.

06:12.266 --> 06:15.633 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And that, in fact, is what
they would do in this bill.

06:15.633 --> 06:19.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The problem, according to the
insurance industry and a lot of
others who oppose it, is that

06:19.733 --> 06:23.400 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
it would make coverage for sick
people pretty much unaffordable.

06:23.400 --> 06:28.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It would leave only sick
people in those plans that
offer all the benefits.

06:28.200 --> 06:32.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For the people who are lucky
enough to get tax credits, and
they have lowered the threshold,

06:32.433 --> 06:35.700 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
those people would be mostly
protected from those increases.

06:35.700 --> 06:40.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But people who are buying their
own insurance and make too much
money to get those tax credits

06:40.566 --> 06:44.200 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
would bear the brunt of those
very much higher premiums.

06:44.200 --> 06:46.700 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So that's a big worry about
how this might play out.

06:46.700 --> 06:50.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, Lisa, and
the leadership was making
this gesture in Senator Cruz's

06:50.833 --> 06:51.833 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
direction.

06:51.833 --> 06:53.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
How is it going over?

06:53.900 --> 06:55.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: These were
intense negotiations to
put this in the bill today.

06:55.933 --> 07:00.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But, Judy, if you actually read
the bill online, the entire
Cruz amendment is in brackets.

07:00.600 --> 07:02.466 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Literally, it is in brackets.

07:02.466 --> 07:05.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And Republican leadership
confirmed that means
it's not final.

07:05.666 --> 07:06.866 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It could still be taken out.

07:06.866 --> 07:08.933 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It could still be revised.

07:08.933 --> 07:12.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And one other tricky piece of
choreography with all of this,
multiple sources have told

07:12.133 --> 07:17.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
me that they are going to get a
score from not CBO -- just from
CBO, but also the Department

07:18.000 --> 07:19.633 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
of Health and Human Services.

07:19.633 --> 07:22.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
which is a very
unusual step on this.

07:22.166 --> 07:25.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They are going to see what
the Department of Health and
Human Services think the Cruz

07:25.000 --> 07:26.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
amendment will mean.

07:26.733 --> 07:29.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
And all of this is kind
of adding new questions
to the process as well.

07:29.666 --> 07:32.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Presumably
not knowing what the
department is going to say.

07:32.833 --> 07:34.733 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Is that right?

07:34.733 --> 07:36.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Or do they assume the department
is going to come in and
say this is a good thing?

07:36.266 --> 07:37.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
LISA DESJARDINS:
That, we don't know.

07:37.933 --> 07:39.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
We know there have
been conversations
for weeks with CBO.

07:39.766 --> 07:42.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
CBO has known the general
outlines of these bills.

07:42.533 --> 07:45.066 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Have they had those
conversations with HHS as well?

07:45.066 --> 07:46.333 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I don't know.

07:46.333 --> 07:48.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Lisa, I
want to stay with you.

07:48.366 --> 07:52.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You have been following this
day after day after day since
the Senate went home for recess.

07:52.800 --> 07:54.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
They have now come back.

07:54.866 --> 07:57.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What is the political calculus
on the part of the Republican
leadership in the Senate?

07:57.500 --> 08:01.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: I think it
comes down to one fact, that
they feel they campaigned on

08:01.266 --> 08:06.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
this and that they have to at
least give it their greatest
try or have to show themselves

08:07.133 --> 08:09.100 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
as trying as hard as possible.

08:09.100 --> 08:11.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Right now, it does look like
it's going to be very difficult
to get the votes for this

08:11.133 --> 08:15.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to pass, but it also looks
like they will hold that vote,
even if it fails, to show

08:15.933 --> 08:19.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
their voters, we tried and
this is as far as we could get.

08:19.233 --> 08:23.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think there is pressure from
both conservatives an moderates
to go both different directions.

08:23.466 --> 08:27.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And that's what making
this goal of reforming and
replacing Obamacare impossible.

08:27.500 --> 08:29.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF:
Julie -- excuse me.

08:29.533 --> 08:32.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Julie, you have done your
own share of reporting
on this for a long time.

08:32.233 --> 08:34.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
What are you seeing
as to where this goes?

08:34.233 --> 08:37.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JULIE ROVNER: I see exactly
