18:18.200 --> 18:20.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
You better do a
good job, please.

18:20.466 --> 18:23.366 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Otherwise, you're going
to make me look very bad.

18:23.366 --> 18:28.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN YANG: The two leaders
said they discussed Syria and
the fight against terrorism.

18:28.200 --> 18:32.933 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Mr. Macron said Mr. Trump's
decision to withdraw
from the Paris climate
accord wouldn't affect

18:32.933 --> 18:34.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
their relationship.

18:34.800 --> 18:38.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Bloomberg News White House
correspondent Toluse Olorunnipa
is covering the trip.

18:38.233 --> 18:41.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TOLUSE OLORUNNIPA, Bloomberg
News: They see the world in
very different ways, but they

18:41.500 --> 18:46.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
have come to realize that
they can benefit from having a
positive relationship with one

18:46.233 --> 18:48.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
another, and that's what
we saw on display today.

18:48.433 --> 18:53.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JOHN YANG: Indeed, the
body language today
was a marked difference
from their first awkward

18:55.333 --> 18:58.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
encounter in May, and
was capped tonight with
dinner at the Eiffel Tower.

19:00.666 --> 19:03.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
After watching Bastille Day
celebrations in Paris tomorrow,
Mr. Trump heads back to the

19:03.800 --> 19:08.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
United States, and more
repercussions from his
son's Russia meeting.

19:08.700 --> 19:12.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Senate Judiciary Committee
Chairman Chuck Grassley said
he wants Donald Trump Jr. to

19:12.900 --> 19:17.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
testify in open session
as soon as next week.

19:17.033 --> 19:19.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
For the "PBS NewsHour,"
I'm John Yang.

19:19.433 --> 19:24.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: As we just heard,
the president defended his older
son's meeting with a Russian

19:24.400 --> 19:28.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
lawyer last year, saying
that it was standard
opposition research.

19:28.800 --> 19:31.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
But some have
questioned that premise.

19:31.133 --> 19:35.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
To discuss all this,
we are joined now by
two campaign veterans.

19:35.033 --> 19:39.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Tim Miller was the former
communications director for Jeb
Bush's presidential campaign.

19:39.833 --> 19:44.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He is also co-founder of
the Republican opposition
research group America Rising.

19:46.866 --> 19:51.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And Christina Reynolds, she
was the deputy communications
director for Hillary Clinton's

19:53.333 --> 19:56.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
2016 presidential campaign,
and she's now the senior vice
president for Global Strategy

19:57.566 --> 20:00.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Group, a Democratic
research firm.

20:00.166 --> 20:01.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And we welcome both of
you to the "NewsHour."

20:01.933 --> 20:03.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Christina, I'm going
to start with you.

20:03.800 --> 20:05.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Tell our audience, what
is opposition research?

20:05.966 --> 20:07.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHRISTINA REYNOLDS, Former
Hillary Clinton Campaign Deputy
Communications Director: Well,

20:07.500 --> 20:09.600 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
when I started, we used to call
it quotes, votes and anecdotes.

20:09.600 --> 20:13.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It is gathering public
information to tell a
story about your opponent.

20:13.666 --> 20:15.666 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
So, we look at public sources.

20:15.666 --> 20:20.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We look at everything from
votes to tax records to personal
stories that you can find out

20:21.100 --> 20:22.600 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
about someone.

20:22.600 --> 20:24.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Tim Miller,
what would you add to that?

20:24.533 --> 20:25.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TIM MILLER, Former Jeb Bush
Campaign Communications
Director: I think that's right.

20:25.666 --> 20:27.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I call it full
information awareness.

20:27.666 --> 20:31.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You want to know everything
you can about your opponent,
everything they have ever said,

20:31.533 --> 20:35.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
any way they have ever made
money, any way they have ever
spent money, and so that you

20:35.900 --> 20:39.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
can use it to your advantage
in the campaign and so voters
know their entire record.

20:39.733 --> 20:43.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And, Christina
Reynolds, is it anything goes?

20:43.800 --> 20:46.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Anything about their medical
records, their personal life?

20:46.300 --> 20:48.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
CHRISTINA REYNOLDS: No.

20:48.400 --> 20:50.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I mean, first and foremost,
you have to -- we used to have
a rule that said, if you can

20:50.700 --> 20:53.233 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
cite it, you can write it.

20:53.233 --> 20:56.966 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You need a publicly
available source for
something to be credible
in the news, for something

20:57.733 --> 20:59.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to be credible in ads.

20:59.800 --> 21:03.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, second of all, if you
go into things like medical
records and things like that,

21:03.433 --> 21:06.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
then you start getting into
worrying about blowback
for your own candidate.

21:06.233 --> 21:07.400 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
So, it's not anything goes.

21:07.400 --> 21:08.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
You have to be careful.

21:08.400 --> 21:09.633 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(CROSSTALK)

21:09.633 --> 21:11.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: What
do you mean blowback?

21:11.700 --> 21:14.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHRISTINA REYNOLDS: I mean,
at some point, there's a risk
that the actual gathering of

21:14.766 --> 21:18.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
the information may be
considered worse then
the public -- than
the information that's

21:18.900 --> 21:21.733 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
found, if it's considered
dirty tricks, so to speak.

21:21.733 --> 21:26.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Tim Miller,
are there lines drawn around
what's considered acceptable

21:26.266 --> 21:28.066 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
opposition research or not?

21:28.066 --> 21:30.066 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
TIM MILLER: Of course there are.

21:30.066 --> 21:34.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We started an opposition
research firm America Rising
that has been very successful.

21:34.400 --> 21:39.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And -- but what try to do is
ensure that we stay inside
these lines, both legal lines

21:40.566 --> 21:42.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
and ethical -- and
ethical boundaries.

21:42.700 --> 21:47.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I think both of those are
in play here with regards to
the president's son's meeting.

21:48.700 --> 21:50.800 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It's like Christina said.

21:50.800 --> 21:55.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You saw this with the Ted Cruz
campaign in Iowa, that they
had blowback when they were

21:57.333 --> 21:59.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
spreading information that Ben
Carson was going to drop out
of the race, when that wasn't

21:59.200 --> 22:01.266 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
true.

22:01.266 --> 22:04.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You have to be careful that
your opposition research is
correct, first and foremost, but

22:04.166 --> 22:06.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
also within legal
and ethical bounds.

22:06.166 --> 22:08.566 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And that's what I
want to pursue with both of you.

22:08.566 --> 22:13.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
What is inside and what
is outside the bounds
of what you can do?

22:15.566 --> 22:18.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, of course, we're asking
you all this because of what
happened with regard to Donald

22:18.166 --> 22:22.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Trump Jr., the meeting
he took with a Russian
- - representative of
the Russian government.

22:22.766 --> 22:24.866 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
CHRISTINA REYNOLDS: Sure.

22:24.866 --> 22:27.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Well, I can tell you, in
my experience in research,
what he did is not normal.

22:27.600 --> 22:32.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think that what's inside
the bounds is things that
are publicly available.

22:34.066 --> 22:36.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
You do a lot of Freedom
of Information Act
records requests.

22:36.800 --> 22:41.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You certainly talk to people,
but you do so with people that
you know and trust are giving

22:43.400 --> 22:46.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
you solid information
and information that you
can then go and prove.

22:46.400 --> 22:51.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And you certainly don't
do something with a
hostile government,
you know, being on your

22:52.933 --> 22:54.966 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
side.

22:54.966 --> 22:58.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You know, the best example of
this is when Al Gore's campaign
got a debate book FedExed

23:00.233 --> 23:02.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
to them, a George
Bush debate book.

23:02.266 --> 23:05.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The first thing they did was
call the FBI, because you
wonder, are you being set up?

23:05.833 --> 23:10.333 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You wonder, is this something
that's valid, that's real?

23:10.333 --> 23:13.166 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That's something that you
don't take every meeting.

23:13.166 --> 23:15.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
People call with tips.

23:15.166 --> 23:18.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You make sure that you
trust the veracity of the
information and the source.

23:18.266 --> 23:23.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Tim Miller, had
you ever, before this instance,
heard of a time when someone

23:23.100 --> 23:26.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
was offered information by a
foreign hostile government?

23:26.433 --> 23:31.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TIM MILLER: Well, I will tell
you, almost to the question,
I -- like President Trump,

23:33.466 --> 23:37.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
have been called by anonymous
people, friends of friends with
information about him, frankly,

23:39.300 --> 23:42.600 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and about Hillary Clinton when
I was working for Jeb Bush.

23:42.600 --> 23:45.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And you have to make a
decision about whether
this is a credible person.

23:45.700 --> 23:49.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You have to talk to lawyers
to make sure, if you have
the conversation, it's within

23:49.733 --> 23:51.700 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
legal bounds.

23:51.700 --> 23:55.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Now, those conversations,
while maybe some would consider
to be a little bit sketchy,

23:57.866 --> 24:01.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
pale in comparison to the idea
of getting a call from somebody
who explicitly says they're

24:02.100 --> 24:03.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
here from the
Russian government.

24:03.500 --> 24:05.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
This is not just a
foreign government, Judy.

24:05.133 --> 24:07.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It wasn't Switzerland who
had called Donald Trump Jr.

24:07.433 --> 24:09.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Right.

24:09.966 --> 24:12.166 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TIM MILLER: It was a
country that is out there
to undermine our interests
on the world stage.

24:12.166 --> 24:16.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's so far beyond the pale,
that it's kind of almost silly
to compare it to some of these

24:16.933 --> 24:20.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
other gray area opposition
research efforts, because
there is nothing gray about it.

24:20.766 --> 24:25.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Christina, were
you ever aware of being offered
or hear of anybody in a campaign

24:25.333 --> 24:27.900 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
being offered something
from a foreign hostile...

24:27.900 --> 24:28.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
CHRISTINA REYNOLDS: From
a foreign government?

24:28.900 --> 24:30.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Right.

24:30.333 --> 24:32.400 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
CHRISTINA REYNOLDS:
That's an easy answer: No.

24:32.400 --> 24:35.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And so, when
a question arises about what
you're -- whether you're being

24:35.300 --> 24:39.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
offered or what someone's trying
to tell you, if there is any
question about it, what do

24:39.933 --> 24:41.933 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
you do?

24:41.933 --> 24:44.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHRISTINA REYNOLDS: I think,
as Tim mentioned, sometimes,
you talk to lawyers.

24:44.733 --> 24:49.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You think about, will I be
able to give this to a reporter
and know that it's true?

24:51.666 --> 24:55.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Would I have my candidate
say it out loud and
feel confident in that?

24:55.200 --> 24:59.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
You think through those
things, and I think you
set a really high bar.

24:59.033 --> 25:02.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If we learned anything from the
Donald Trump's election, from
the past campaign and Trump's

25:02.533 --> 25:07.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
election, it's that no one
story can kill a campaign, but
you don't want to be the one

25:08.966 --> 25:11.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that is -- you know, that is
seen as playing dirty tricks.

25:11.933 --> 25:16.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Are people
-- I know every campaign is
different, Tim Miller, in the

25:18.133 --> 25:20.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
way it's organized, the
hierarchy and so forth.

25:20.433 --> 25:25.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But are there rules that are
shared, that are known by people
in modern American politics

25:26.366 --> 25:29.233 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
about what's OK and what isn't?

25:29.233 --> 25:31.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
You just count on
the lawyers you hire?

25:31.500 --> 25:36.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I know every campaign
has lawyers to tell you
that, or how does that work?

25:36.333 --> 25:40.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TIM MILLER: Yes, look, I
think that there are norms
within opposition research.

25:40.500 --> 25:42.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
We also run a candidate
tracking organization.

25:42.633 --> 25:47.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's the guys that -- and gals
that follow around candidates
with a video camera to get

25:48.500 --> 25:50.033 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
whatever they say on the record.

25:50.033 --> 25:52.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And there are rules.

25:52.633 --> 25:56.033 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We work with a Democratic
opposition research firm,
you know, and we would
have an off-the-record

25:58.066 --> 26:02.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
conversation to kind of set
boundaries, you know, that we
weren't going to go videotape

26:02.600 --> 26:04.533 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
their family dinner, right?

26:04.533 --> 26:09.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You're not going to go
dumpster-diving in there in the
trash can outside their house.

26:11.300 --> 26:14.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Like I said, there are going to
be areas where there are some
-- where there are gray areas.

26:14.833 --> 26:18.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Opposition research is not
all just fun and games.

26:18.300 --> 26:22.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
It's serious business,
especially running
for high office.

26:22.266 --> 26:27.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But there are legal lines and
then there are also just decency
boundaries, you know, like

26:28.366 --> 26:30.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
the example I mentioned
about the family.

26:30.466 --> 26:34.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Right, but even
if -- Christina, even if the
campaign says, we're not going

26:36.266 --> 26:39.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to do this, there are other
tabloids and others out there
who may be engaging in this kind

26:40.133 --> 26:41.066 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of research.

26:41.066 --> 26:43.133 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
CHRISTINA REYNOLDS: Sure.

26:43.133 --> 26:46.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I think one thing -- Tim
will probably back me up on
this -- one thing that is true

26:46.200 --> 26:49.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of all researchers
is, we all see black
helicopters a little bit.

26:49.933 --> 26:51.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
We are all just a
little bit paranoid.

26:51.833 --> 26:54.500 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And you worry about a setup.

26:54.500 --> 26:58.700 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You worry that just the
giving of that information
may be more interesting
news than the information

27:00.200 --> 27:01.666 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
itself.

27:01.666 --> 27:05.200 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And so you use your best
judgment, as Tim mentioned.

27:05.200 --> 27:09.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You know, you use your lawyers
and you use your best judgment,
and you make sure that

27:09.766 --> 27:11.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
you don't do anything that's
going to damage the campaign.

27:11.533 --> 27:13.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF:
Experience counts.

27:13.666 --> 27:17.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
TIM MILLER: You go back
to that '08 campaign
with Hillary Clinton and
Obama, Hillary Clinton's

27:17.366 --> 27:22.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
oppo research on Obama, I think
-- Christina would know better
-- backfired more than it

27:22.100 --> 27:27.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
helped, because people didn't
want there to be, within a
family, intraparty squabbles

27:28.666 --> 27:29.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
that were that personal.

27:29.933 --> 27:33.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And so you have to be
careful about that.

27:33.000 --> 27:37.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
