33:14.666 --> 33:16.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
MASHA GESSEN: Well, I
am certainly an enemy
of the mafia state.

33:16.433 --> 33:17.666 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Absolutely, yes.

33:17.666 --> 33:20.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I'm not an enemy of
the Russian state.

33:20.066 --> 33:23.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
NICK SCHIFRIN: Gessen
was the first journalist
blacklisted by Putin's Kremlin.

33:23.733 --> 33:27.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She's also been targeted
because she's a lesbian who's
raising adopted children.

33:27.033 --> 33:31.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOMAN (through translator):
He was born by a woman I don't
know and first met when he

33:31.766 --> 33:33.866 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
was 2.

33:33.866 --> 33:37.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
NICK SCHIFRIN: In 2013,
she helped lead a video
campaign criticizing
an anti-gay propaganda

33:37.733 --> 33:39.766 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
law.

33:39.766 --> 33:43.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It helped condone homophobia
and attacks on gay Russians, and
Gessen argues the law explains

33:43.366 --> 33:45.466 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
how Putin rules.

33:45.466 --> 33:49.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MASHA GESSEN: The autocrat
needs everybody out in the
street with flags aloft.

33:50.566 --> 33:52.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
